============================================================

The improvement plan is written to `tools/title-loop/docs/22-480d364/improvement-plan.md`.

**Summary of the 8 proposed changes, ranked by impact:**

1. **Colon filter** (Change 7A) — One-line addition to `passesHardFilters`: reject any candidate ending with `:`. Recipe titles never end with colons; section headers always do. Fixes ~5 Pattern 7 failures instantly.

2. **OCR normalization post-processing** (Change 1) — New `normalizeOcrTitle()` function applied to the final output. Fixes `1→I/l`, `0→O`, `4→A`, `¡→i` substitutions + title-case conversion. Fixes all 11 Pattern 1 failures with zero regression risk.

3. **Page/section header filtering** (Change 2) — Add `Page \d+`/`Strona \d+` patterns and English food category names to hard filters. Fixes all 6 Pattern 2 failures.

4. **Remove compound-variant stripping** (Change 4) — Delete lines 999-1009 that truncate `A : B` titles when both halves share a first word. Fixes 3-4 Pattern 4 failures.

5. **Overflow preamble detection** (Change 3) — Extend `findBurstEnd` to skip PREVIOUS/OVERFLOW/SPILLOVER markers. Fixes 2 Pattern 3 failures.

6. **Hyphen-continuation + multi-line join improvements** (Change 5) — Join hyphen-broken lines, relax caps coalescing, remove "placki" from SECTION_LABELS. Fixes 3-4 Pattern 5 failures.

7. **Annotation line filtering + OCR-aware embedding** (Change 6) — Skip `(OCR CORRUPTION: ...)` lines, normalize candidates before embedding. Fixes 4-5 Pattern 6 failures.

8. **Minimum confidence floor** (Change 8) — Return `undefined` instead of random fallback when no candidate scores above 0.02. Fixes the 1 Pattern 8 case correctly.

Expected total: **36-40 of 40 failures fixed**.
