{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01E5pUGQe2Gbzn34UfcB3267","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→PREVIOUS RECIPE OVERFLOW:\n     2→[Page 47 - Recipe Continuation]\n     3→...and fold in the remaining walnuts. The batter should be thick enough\n     4→to hold its shape but still pourable. Add ½ cup plus ı tablespoon of\n     5→buttermilk if too thick. Pour into prepped loaf pan and bake at 160°C\n     6→for 45-50 minutes until a toothpick comes out clean.\n     7→\n     8→Cool in the pan for 10 minutes, then turn out onto a wire rack. The\n     9→crust should be golden-brown and crispy when properly baked. Some\n    10→recipes call for a dusting of powdered sugar or a glaze of melted white\n    11→chocolate mixed with coconut oil.\n    12→\n    13→The texture should be moist throughout, not dry or crumbly. This is often\n    14→a sign that too much flour was incorporated or baking time was excessive.\n    15→\n    16→Remove any excess crumbs from the coun-ter and wash your hands before\n    17→beginning the next preparation. Make sure all equipment is clean before\n    18→proceeding to avoid cross-contamination of flavors.\n    19→\n    20→CORRUPTED SECTION: jkQpMn vhtyWz XfGhJ pQrStU vWxYzA bCdEfG\n    21→Page 48\n    22→====================================================================\n    23→\n    24→BEET AND GOAT CHEESE SALAD\n    25→\n    26→INGREDIENTS:\n    27→• 4 medium red beets, roasted and peeled\n    28→• 150g fresh goat cheese, crumbled\n    29→• 4 cups mixed salad greens (arugula, spinach, romaine)\n    30→• ¼ cup toasted walnuts, roughly chopped"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_015NC4qY23ghoCGyD62h8XkS","session_id":"52c225dd-138d-420c-8852-ee28a481d2ae","uuid":"90a3d05b-a3c2-4659-a9b5-697e9264b0a5"}
