{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011NQc1grBNapaDN2hmyoUMR","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→LEMON CURD : LEMON CURD WITH THYME (VARIATION)\n     2→\n     3→CLASSIC LEMON CURD\n     4→\n     5→Ingredients:\n     6→- 6 egg yolks\n     7→- 3/4 cup granulated sugar\n     8→- 1/2 cup fresh lemon juice\n     9→- 2 tablespoons lemon zest\n    10→- 1/4 teaspoon salt\n    11→- 6 tablespoons butter, cubed\n    12→- 1/4 teaspoon vanilla extract\n    13→\n    14→Instructions for Classic:\n    15→Whisk together egg yolks and sugar in heat-safe bowl.\n    16→Add lemon juice, zest, and salt.\n    17→Set bowl over pot of simmering water (double boiler).\n    18→Whisk constantly for 12-15 minutes until thickened.\n    19→Temperature should reach 160°F for food safety.\n    20→Remove from heat.\n    21→Whisk in butter cubes one at a time until melted and smooth.\n    22→Add vanilla extract.\n    23→Strain through fine sieve to remove any cooked egg bits.\n    24→Transfer to sterilized jars.\n    25→Cool to room temperature before refrigerating.\n    26→\n    27→---\n    28→\n    29→VARIATION: LEMON CURD WITH THYME\n    30→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_015NC4qY23ghoCGyD62h8XkS","session_id":"52c225dd-138d-420c-8852-ee28a481d2ae","uuid":"752a3bbb-bc53-45a8-9259-0e72f2f3459c"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BDj2bXnSWK83c4dxquHT3z","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→ROSEMARY\n     2→FOCACCIA\n     3→BREAD\n     4→\n     5→Makes 2 loaves | Active time: 20 min | Passive time: 2-3 hours (includes proofing)\n     6→\n     7→DOUGH:\n     8→500g strong bread flour\n     9→350ml warm water\n    10→7g instant yeast\n    11→10g salt\n    12→30ml olive oil\n    13→\n    14→TOPPING:\n    15→6 tbsp olive oil\n    16→3 tbsp coarse sea salt\n    17→4 sprigs fresh rosemary\n    18→Cracked black pepper\n    19→\n    20→METHOD - DOUGH:\n    21→1. In large bowl, combine flour, yeast, and salt. Mix well.\n    22→2. Add water and oil. Mix until shaggy dough forms.\n    23→3. Knead by hand for 10 minutes or with stand mixer for 6 minutes until smooth and elastic.\n    24→4. Place in oiled bowl, cover with damp cloth. Let rise at room temperature for 90 minutes until doubled.\n    25→\n    26→SHAPING:\n    27→1. Turn dough onto lightly floured surface. Divide into two equal pieces.\n    28→2. Shape each into a rough rectangle about 25cm x 20cm.\n    29→3. Transfer to two oiled sheet pans or one large pan.\n    30→4. Cover loosely and let rise for 60 minutes until puffy."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_015NC4qY23ghoCGyD62h8XkS","session_id":"52c225dd-138d-420c-8852-ee28a481d2ae","uuid":"935df64e-9bd6-44c0-96b3-2826e0729dd7"}
