{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Fh5LKDndYvRMYbM5tbd3Sw","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→Golonka\n     2→Roasted Pork Knuckle\n     3→\n     4→Ingredients:\n     5→- 2 pork knuckles (about 3-4 lbs each)\n     6→- 2 tablespoons caraway seeds\n     7→- 4 cloves garlic, minced\n     8→- 2 tablespoons Dijon mustard\n     9→- 2 tablespoons honey\n    10→- 2 tablespoons soy sauce\n    11→- 1 tablespoon paprika\n    12→- 1 teaspoon marjoram\n    13→- Salt and pepper to taste\n    14→- 2 cups beef or pork stock\n    15→- 2 cups root vegetables (carrots, parsnips, onions)\n    16→- 2 bay leaves\n    17→- 1 tablespoon cornstarch\n    18→- 3 tablespoons water\n    19→\n    20→Instructions:\n    21→\n    22→Preparation:\n    23→Score the skin of pork knuckles in crosshatch pattern.\n    24→Pat dry with paper towels.\n    25→\n    26→Marinade:\n    27→Combine mustard, honey, soy sauce, paprika, marjoram in bowl.\n    28→Mix in minced garlic and caraway seeds.\n    29→Rub mixture all over knuckles.\n    30→Season generously with salt and pepper."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_015NC4qY23ghoCGyD62h8XkS","session_id":"52c225dd-138d-420c-8852-ee28a481d2ae","uuid":"3164c43a-c032-4dd4-88a0-9e10ba09affe"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WErbLDHAG6U7bc97iVtZDT","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→MAKOWIEC\n     2→(Poppy Seed Cake)\n     3→\n     4→Czas przygotowania: 30 minut | Czas gotowania: 50 minut | Liczba porcji: 10-12\n     5→\n     6→CIASTO:\n     7→250g mąki pszennej\n     8→100g zmielonego maku (makowiny)\n     9→150g cukru\n    10→100g masła, rozmięckiego\n    11→3 jaja\n    12→100ml mleka\n    13→2 tsp proszku do pieczenia\n    14→1 tsp ekstraktu waniliowego\n    15→Szczypta soli\n    16→Skórka cytryny, otarta\n    17→2 łyżki mleka (do posypki)\n    18→1 łyżka cukru trzcinowego\n    19→\n    20→PASTA MAKOWA:\n    21→300g maku zmielonego\n    22→150g cukru\n    23→100g mleka\n    24→50g masła\n    25→1 żółtko jaja\n    26→½ tsp ekstraktu waniliowego\n    27→\n    28→METODA:\n    29→\n    30→1. Rozgrzać piekarnik do 175°C. Posmować foremkę prostokątną (30x20cm) i wyłożyć papierem do pieczenia."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_015NC4qY23ghoCGyD62h8XkS","session_id":"52c225dd-138d-420c-8852-ee28a481d2ae","uuid":"79c1a756-3912-403a-909d-16cfbd2fc1e4"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NSeWrxnHGhMhFTFdEkcE7Y","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→2 large sweet potatoes, peeled and cut into 2cm cubes\n     2→4 cups fresh spinach leaves\n     3→½ red onion, thinly sliced\n     4→½ cup roasted walnuts, roughly chopped\n     5→¼ cup dried cranberries\n     6→½ cup crumbled goat cheese or feta\n     7→\n     8→For dressing:\n     9→3 tablespoons extra virgin olive oil\n    10→1½ tablespoons balsamic vinegar\n    11→1 tablespoon maple syrup\n    12→1 teaspoon Dijon mustard\n    13→Salt and pepper to taste\n    14→\n    15→Method:\n    16→Preheat oven to 200°C. Toss sweet potato cubes with olive oil, salt, and pepper. Spread on\n    17→baking tray in single layer. Roast for 25-30 minutes until golden and tender, stirring halfway\n    18→through cooking time.\n    19→\n    20→While potatoes roast, whisk together dressing ingredients in small bowl until emulsified.\n    21→Season to taste with salt and freshly ground black pepper.\n    22→\n    23→In large salad bowl, combine spinach, sliced red onion, and fresh greens. Add roasted sweet\n    24→potatoes while still warm. Drizzle dressing over salad and toss gently to combine. Top with\n    25→walnuts, cranberries, and crumbled goat cheese.\n    26→\n    27→Serve immediately while potatoes are still slightly warm, or chill before serving.\n    28→\n    29→Sweet Potato Salad\n    30→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_015NC4qY23ghoCGyD62h8XkS","session_id":"52c225dd-138d-420c-8852-ee28a481d2ae","uuid":"0df50269-f874-4985-b89e-1a9c19db0976"}
