→Method:\n    16→Preheat oven to 200°C. Toss sweet potato cubes with olive oil, salt, and pepper. Spread on\n    17→baking tray in single layer. Roast for 25-30 minutes until golden and tender, stirring halfway\n    18→through cooking time.\n    19→\n    20→While potatoes roast, whisk together dressing ingredients in small bowl until emulsified.\n    21→Season to taste with salt and freshly ground black pepper.\n    22→\n    23→In large salad bowl, combine spinach, sliced red onion, and fresh greens. Add roasted sweet\n    24→potatoes while still warm. Drizzle dressing over salad and toss gently to combine. Top with\n    25→walnuts, cranberries, and crumbled goat cheese.\n    26→\n    27→Serve immediately while potatoes are still slightly warm, or chill before serving.\n    28→\n    29→Sweet Potato Salad\n    30→\n```\n\n## 11. Profiteroles.generated.22.txt\n```\n     1→PROFITEROLES\n     2→chapter 3 | page 52\n     3→\n     4→Choux pastry ingredients:\n     5→- 1 cup water\n     6→- 1/2 cup butter\n     7→- 1/4 teaspoon salt\n     8→- 1 cup all-purpose flour\n     9→- 4 eggs\n    10→\n    11→Chocolate sauce:\n    12→- 8 oz semisweet chocolate [53], chopped\n    13→- 1/2 cup heavy cream\n    14→- 2 tablespoons butter\n    15→- 1 tablespoon corn syrup\n    16→- 1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract\n    17→\n    18→Filling:\n    19→- 2 cups heavy cream\n    20→- 3 tablespoons powdered sugar\n    21→- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n    22→\n    23→Directions for choux paste:\n    24→\n    25→Preheat oven 400°F. Line baking sheet with parchment.\n    26→\n    27→Bring water, butter, salt to boil. Remove heat. Stir in flour\n    28→all at once, mixing until paste forms and pulls away from pan sides\n    29→[text smudged]. Cool 5 minutes.\n    30→\n```\n\n## 12. Mushroom Risotto.generated.22.txt\n```\n     1→Reduce heat and stir in the remaining stock, one ladle at a time, until the rice is\n     2→creamy but still al dente, about 18-20 minutes. The risotto should flow slightly on the plate.\n     3→Season with salt and white pepper. Finish with butter and grated Parmigiano-Reggiano.\n     4→\n     5→CARPACCIO DI PESCE SPADA\n     6→\n     7→Slice the swordfish paper-thin. Arrange on chilled plates. Dress with extra virgin olive oil,\n     8→lemon juice, and sea salt. Scatter thinly shaved fennel and microgreens. Serve immediately.\n     9→\n    10→Preparation: 10 minutes\n    11→Serves: 4\n    12→\n    13→CARPACCIO WITH CITRUS DRESSING\n    14→\n    15→Place thin slices on a cold plate. Whisk together lemon, lime, orange juice with good quality\n    16→oil. Season with fıne sea salt and crushed coriander seeds. Garnish with fresh herbs and\n    17→thinly sliced radish.\n    18→\n    19→nto a loured work counter and knead until smooth, approx 8 minutes. Proof in oiled bowl, cover\n    20→with damp cloth, 45 minutes at room temperature. Shape into ½ dozen rounds. Second proof 30 min.\n    21→\n    22→Place pans in 225°C/435-VI0.. oven for 12-15 minutes until golden brown. Cool on wire rack.\n    23→\n    24→Makes: 1 dozen\n    25→\n    26→FRESH PASTA DOUGH\n    27→\n    28→125 grams plain flour\n    29→½ cup plus ı tablespoon water\n    30→Pinch of sea salt\n```\n\nThese files showcase typical OCR corruption patterns with digit-for-letter substitutions (0 for O, 1 for I), hyphenation errors, spillover content from previous recipes, and garbled text sections."}],"totalDurationMs":53142,"totalTokens":101490,"totalToolUseCount":12,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7467,"cache_read_input_tokens":88797,"output_tokens":5219,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":7467},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
